I am not sure which propulsion system I will choose to use, EPPP is always a possibility, as are NTR's, and I have been reading some of Chang Diaz's papers on VASMIR to get more technical details on it. It will be fast, for safety's sake, we can't have 12 month transits like Energia's 600 ton solar hall thruster snail or Zubrin's 6 months in spinning tuna can. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 412<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/15/02 11:55:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Mars Mission</span><hr size=1> How &quot;surprising&quot; that Darth Vader himself says we shouldn't have nukes in space!  If that's not a sign that anti-nuclear activists are totalitarians I don't know what is!!  <br>
